data.text:
@SallyRMelb @MargMcCrohon we should be hearing about #auspol every news hour bc it is so important, but ABC just decides to ignore it entirely.

Not good enough imho.
@SallyRMelb @MargMcCrohon no ive only been listening to it since my brother inflicted it on me.

@CharlizeTheroff @MargMcCrohon It's not nearly a real thing yet and may not even happen. I don't think yet another round of 'maybe possibly' there'll be a #libspill is news. But its worthy of commentary and I think it's getting that. Do you have abclistenapp ? Eg Fran Kelly breakfast prog Fri morn
@SallyRMelb @MargMcCrohon it should be on the news, it affects all of us in so many ways.
@CharlizeTheroff @MargMcCrohon It's not always on news. I heard bits of interviews & comments about dissatisfaction with Malcolm throughout day& evening on ABC newsRadio & RN.
@lukehart78 @CharlizeTheroff Fair enough. The bar is set so low, I tend to support any action of the media that might be construed as responsible behaviour. Call me a hopeless optimist I guess. 😁😁

@davem3393 @CharlizeTheroff Echo chamber speculation with nothing solid? Could say the same thing about the whole Shorten versus Albanese nonsense. Didn't stop the ABC joining the echo chamber then. Why stop now?

@CharlizeTheroff Maybe because #libSpill at the moment is the equivalent of the super saturday by-election coverage? Lots of echo chamber speculation with little or nothing solid. The only 'fact' is that Ray Hadley says it's on, but he'll say most anything to get ratings.
@CharlizeTheroff @deniseshrivell Thanks @deniseshrivell this has been super useful!!! Thanks for your great contribution yesterday 💯🙏🌟 #WomenInTheHouse
